{"author":{"id":"f5e6fb13f9693ecb1a1489d317dc9e92d66dc33540e202741cbd9f83af526090"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1578027657,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1NDQ4NTE1MDQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/MichaelMure/git-bug/issues/284","origin":"github"},"nonce":"4jwVo7Pt+CXn2WSiTAZYu+V+gSA=","title":"Pushing to a bridge does not push comments added via git-bug.","message":"## To Reproduce\n\n1. Pull from bug tracker (in my case, self-hosted GitLab) using bridge\n1. Adopt an identity created when pulling via bridge\n1. Comment on one of the existing issues locally using git-bug\n1. Push to bug tracker using bridge\n\n## Expected\n\nComment added to issue locally using git-bug should be present on issue in bug tracker (based on [this](https://github.com/MichaelMure/git-bug#exporter-implementations)).\n\n## Actual\n\nComment not present on issue in bug tracker, but present when inspecting the issue locally using git-bug.\n\nI've only tested with the GitLab bridge (and a self-hosted version of GitLab at that), so I'm not sure if the same thing happens with the other available bridges (or with the main gitlab.com).","files":null}]}